# Rooms Documentation

When modifying room mode or occupancy files, the documentation at `docs/ROOMS.md` may need updates.

## Before Completing Changes

Review if your changes affect any of these documented areas:

| Area | What to Check |
|------|---------------|
| **Room Modes** | New modes, mode behavior changes, mode transitions |
| **Occupancy Triggers** | New sensors, trigger conditions, detection methods |
| **Occupied/Unoccupied Actions** | Light behavior, media control, TTS routing |
| **Room-Specific Patterns** | DnD mode, Bedtime mode, Wake mode variations |
| **Linking to House State** | How rooms respond to house-level changes |

## Mode Files Pattern

Room modes follow this naming pattern:
- `{room}_mode_auto.yaml` - Auto mode behaviors
- `{room}_mode_off.yaml` - Off mode behaviors
- `{room}_mode_dnd.yaml` - Do Not Disturb mode
- `{room}_mode_bedtime.yaml` - Bedtime mode
- `{room}_occupied.yaml` - Occupancy on trigger
- `{room}_not_occupied.yaml` - Occupancy off trigger

## Action Required

After making changes, ask the user:

> "I've modified room mode/occupancy logic. Should I review and update `docs/ROOMS.md` to reflect these changes?"

If the user agrees, read the current documentation and update any sections affected by the changes.
